552@implementation WebAccessibilityObjectWrapper
553
554- (void)unregisterUniqueIdForUIElement
555{
556 ASSERT(isMainThread());
557 NSAccessibilityUnregisterUniqueIdForUIElement(self);
558}
559
560- (void)detach
561{
562 // Send unregisterUniqueIdForUIElement unconditionally because if it is
563 // ever accidentally not done (via other bugs in our AX implementation) you
564 // end up with a crash like <rdar://problem/4273149>. It is safe and not
565 // expensive to send even if the object is not registered.
566 [self unregisterUniqueIdForUIElement];
567 [super detach];
568}
569
570- (id)attachmentView
571{
572 return Accessibility::retrieveAutoreleasedValueFromMainThread<id>([protectedSelf = retainPtr(self)] () -> RetainPtr<id> {
573 auto* backingObject = protectedSelf.get().axBackingObject;
574 if (!backingObject)
575 return nil;
576
577 auto* widget = backingObject->widgetForAttachmentView();
578 return widget ? NSAccessibilityUnignoredDescendant(widget->platformWidget()) : nil;
579 });
580}

584static inline BOOL AXObjectIsTextMarker(id object)
585{
586 return object && CFGetTypeID((__bridge CFTypeRef)object) == AXTextMarkerGetTypeID();
587}
588
589static inline BOOL AXObjectIsTextMarkerRange(id object)
590{
591 return object && CFGetTypeID((__bridge CFTypeRef)object) == AXTextMarkerRangeGetTypeID();
592}
593
594#pragma mark Other helpers
595
596- (IntRect)screenToContents:(const IntRect&)rect
597{
598 ASSERT(isMainThread());
599
600 Document* document = self.axBackingObject->document();
601 if (!document)
602 return IntRect();
603
604 FrameView* frameView = document->view();
605 if (!frameView)
606 return IntRect();
607
608 IntPoint startPoint = frameView->screenToContents(rect.minXMaxYCorner());
609 IntPoint endPoint = frameView->screenToContents(rect.maxXMinYCorner());
610 return IntRect(startPoint.x(), startPoint.y(), endPoint.x() - startPoint.x(), endPoint.y() - startPoint.y());
611}

613#pragma mark Select text helpers

615// To be deprecated.
616static std::pair<AccessibilitySearchTextCriteria, AccessibilityTextOperation> accessibilityTextCriteriaForParameterizedAttribute(const NSDictionary *parameterizedAttribute)
617{
618 AccessibilitySearchTextCriteria criteria;
619 AccessibilityTextOperation operation;
620
621 NSString *activityParameter = [parameterizedAttribute objectForKey:NSAccessibilitySelectTextActivity];
622 NSString *ambiguityResolutionParameter = [parameterizedAttribute objectForKey:NSAccessibilitySelectTextAmbiguityResolution];
623 NSString *replacementStringParameter = [parameterizedAttribute objectForKey:NSAccessibilitySelectTextReplacementString];
624 NSArray *searchStringsParameter = [parameterizedAttribute objectForKey:NSAccessibilitySelectTextSearchStrings];
625
626 if ([activityParameter isKindOfClass:[NSString class]]) {
627 if ([activityParameter isEqualToString:NSAccessibilitySelectTextActivityFindAndReplace])
628 operation.type = AccessibilityTextOperationType::Replace;
629 else if ([activityParameter isEqualToString:kAXSelectTextActivityFindAndCapitalize])
630 operation.type = AccessibilityTextOperationType::Capitalize;
631 else if ([activityParameter isEqualToString:kAXSelectTextActivityFindAndLowercase])
632 operation.type = AccessibilityTextOperationType::Lowercase;
633 else if ([activityParameter isEqualToString:kAXSelectTextActivityFindAndUppercase])
634 operation.type = AccessibilityTextOperationType::Uppercase;
635 }
636
637 criteria.direction = AccessibilitySearchTextDirection::Closest;
638 if ([ambiguityResolutionParameter isKindOfClass:[NSString class]]) {
639 if ([ambiguityResolutionParameter isEqualToString:NSAccessibilitySelectTextAmbiguityResolutionClosestAfterSelection])
640 criteria.direction = AccessibilitySearchTextDirection::Forward;
641 else if ([ambiguityResolutionParameter isEqualToString:NSAccessibilitySelectTextAmbiguityResolutionClosestBeforeSelection])
642 criteria.direction = AccessibilitySearchTextDirection::Backward;
643 }
644
645 if ([replacementStringParameter isKindOfClass:[NSString class]])
646 operation.replacementText = replacementStringParameter;
647
648 if ([searchStringsParameter isKindOfClass:[NSArray class]])
649 criteria.searchStrings = makeVector<String>(searchStringsParameter);
650
651 return std::make_pair(criteria, operation);
652}
653
654static AccessibilitySearchTextCriteria accessibilitySearchTextCriteriaForParameterizedAttribute(const NSDictionary *params)
655{
656 AccessibilitySearchTextCriteria criteria;
657
658 NSArray *searchStrings = [params objectForKey:NSAccessibilitySearchTextSearchStrings];
659 NSString *start = [params objectForKey:NSAccessibilitySearchTextStartFrom];
660 NSString *direction = [params objectForKey:NSAccessibilitySearchTextDirection];
661
662 if ([searchStrings isKindOfClass:[NSArray class]])
663 criteria.searchStrings = makeVector<String>(searchStrings);
664
665 if ([start isKindOfClass:[NSString class]]) {
666 if ([start isEqualToString:NSAccessibilitySearchTextStartFromBegin])
667 criteria.start = AccessibilitySearchTextStartFrom::Begin;
668 else if ([start isEqualToString:NSAccessibilitySearchTextStartFromEnd])
669 criteria.start = AccessibilitySearchTextStartFrom::End;
670 }
671
672 if ([direction isKindOfClass:[NSString class]]) {
673 if ([direction isEqualToString:NSAccessibilitySearchTextDirectionBackward])
674 criteria.direction = AccessibilitySearchTextDirection::Backward;
675 else if ([direction isEqualToString:NSAccessibilitySearchTextDirectionClosest])
676 criteria.direction = AccessibilitySearchTextDirection::Closest;
677 else if ([direction isEqualToString:NSAccessibilitySearchTextDirectionAll])
678 criteria.direction = AccessibilitySearchTextDirection::All;
679 }
680
681 return criteria;
682}
683
684static AccessibilityTextOperation accessibilityTextOperationForParameterizedAttribute(AXObjectCache* axObjectCache, const NSDictionary *parameterizedAttribute)
685{
686 AccessibilityTextOperation operation;
687
688 NSArray *markerRanges = [parameterizedAttribute objectForKey:NSAccessibilityTextOperationMarkerRanges];
689 NSString *operationType = [parameterizedAttribute objectForKey:NSAccessibilityTextOperationType];
690 NSString *replacementString = [parameterizedAttribute objectForKey:NSAccessibilityTextOperationReplacementString];
691
692 if ([markerRanges isKindOfClass:[NSArray class]]) {
693 operation.textRanges = makeVector(markerRanges, [&axObjectCache] (id markerRange) {
694 ASSERT(AXObjectIsTextMarkerRange(markerRange));
695 return rangeForTextMarkerRange(axObjectCache, (AXTextMarkerRangeRef)markerRange);
696 });
697 }
698
699 if ([operationType isKindOfClass:[NSString class]]) {
700 if ([operationType isEqualToString:NSAccessibilityTextOperationReplace])
701 operation.type = AccessibilityTextOperationType::Replace;
702 else if ([operationType isEqualToString:NSAccessibilityTextOperationCapitalize])
703 operation.type = AccessibilityTextOperationType::Capitalize;
704 else if ([operationType isEqualToString:NSAccessibilityTextOperationLowercase])
705 operation.type = AccessibilityTextOperationType::Lowercase;
706 else if ([operationType isEqualToString:NSAccessibilityTextOperationUppercase])
707 operation.type = AccessibilityTextOperationType::Uppercase;
708 }
709
710 if ([replacementString isKindOfClass:[NSString class]])
711 operation.replacementText = replacementString;
712
713 return operation;
714}

716static std::pair<std::optional<SimpleRange>, AccessibilitySearchDirection> accessibilityMisspellingSearchCriteriaForParameterizedAttribute(AXObjectCache* axObjectCache, const NSDictionary *params)
717{
718 ASSERT(isMainThread());
719
720 std::pair<std::optional<SimpleRange>, AccessibilitySearchDirection> criteria;
721
722 ASSERT(AXObjectIsTextMarkerRange([params objectForKey:@"AXStartTextMarkerRange"]));
723 criteria.first = rangeForTextMarkerRange(axObjectCache, (AXTextMarkerRangeRef)[params objectForKey:@"AXStartTextMarkerRange"]);
724
725 NSNumber *forward = [params objectForKey:NSAccessibilitySearchTextDirection];
726 if ([forward isKindOfClass:[NSNumber class]])
727 criteria.second = [forward boolValue] ? AccessibilitySearchDirection::Next : AccessibilitySearchDirection::Previous;
728 else
729 criteria.second = AccessibilitySearchDirection::Next;
730
731 return criteria;
732}

798// When modifying attributed strings, the range can come from a source which may provide faulty information (e.g. the spell checker).
799// To protect against such cases the range should be validated before adding or removing attributes.
800static BOOL AXAttributedStringRangeIsValid(NSAttributedString *attrString, NSRange range)
801{
802 return (range.location < [attrString length] && NSMaxRange(range) <= [attrString length]);
803}

805static void AXAttributeStringSetFont(NSMutableAttributedString *attrString, NSString *attribute, CTFontRef font, NSRange range)
806{
807 if (!AXAttributedStringRangeIsValid(attrString, range))
808 return;
809
810 if (font) {
811 NSDictionary *dictionary = @{
812 NSAccessibilityFontNameKey: (__bridge NSString *)adoptCF(CTFontCopyPostScriptName(font)).get(),
813 NSAccessibilityFontFamilyKey: (__bridge NSString *)adoptCF(CTFontCopyFamilyName(font)).get(),
814 NSAccessibilityVisibleNameKey: (__bridge NSString *)adoptCF(CTFontCopyDisplayName(font)).get(),
815 NSAccessibilityFontSizeKey: @(CTFontGetSize(font)),
816 };
817 [attrString addAttribute:attribute value:dictionary range:range];
818 } else
819 [attrString removeAttribute:attribute range:range];
820
821}

848static void AXAttributeStringSetStyle(NSMutableAttributedString* attrString, RenderObject* renderer, NSRange range)
849{
850 const RenderStyle& style = renderer->style();
851
852 // set basic font info
853 AXAttributeStringSetFont(attrString, NSAccessibilityFontTextAttribute, style.fontCascade().primaryFont().getCTFont(), range);
854
855 // set basic colors
856 AXAttributeStringSetColor(attrString, NSAccessibilityForegroundColorTextAttribute, nsColor(style.visitedDependentColor(CSSPropertyColor)), range);
857 AXAttributeStringSetColor(attrString, NSAccessibilityBackgroundColorTextAttribute, nsColor(style.visitedDependentColor(CSSPropertyBackgroundColor)), range);
858
859 // set super/sub scripting
860 VerticalAlign alignment = style.verticalAlign();
861 if (alignment == VerticalAlign::Sub)
862 AXAttributeStringSetNumber(attrString, NSAccessibilitySuperscriptTextAttribute, @(-1), range);
863 else if (alignment == VerticalAlign::Super)
864 AXAttributeStringSetNumber(attrString, NSAccessibilitySuperscriptTextAttribute, @(1), range);
865 else
866 [attrString removeAttribute:NSAccessibilitySuperscriptTextAttribute range:range];
867
868 // set shadow
869 if (style.textShadow())
870 AXAttributeStringSetNumber(attrString, NSAccessibilityShadowTextAttribute, @YES, range);
871 else
872 [attrString removeAttribute:NSAccessibilityShadowTextAttribute range:range];
873
874 // set underline and strikethrough
875 auto decor = style.textDecorationsInEffect();
876 if (!(decor & TextDecoration::Underline)) {
877 [attrString removeAttribute:NSAccessibilityUnderlineTextAttribute range:range];
878 [attrString removeAttribute:NSAccessibilityUnderlineColorTextAttribute range:range];
879 }
880
881 if (!(decor & TextDecoration::LineThrough)) {
882 [attrString removeAttribute:NSAccessibilityStrikethroughTextAttribute range:range];
883 [attrString removeAttribute:NSAccessibilityStrikethroughColorTextAttribute range:range];
884 }
885
886 if (decor & TextDecoration::Underline || decor & TextDecoration::LineThrough) {
887 // FIXME: Should the underline style be reported here?
888 auto decorationStyles = TextDecorationPainter::stylesForRenderer(*renderer, decor);
889
890 if (decor & TextDecoration::Underline) {
891 AXAttributeStringSetNumber(attrString, NSAccessibilityUnderlineTextAttribute, @YES, range);
892 AXAttributeStringSetColor(attrString, NSAccessibilityUnderlineColorTextAttribute, nsColor(decorationStyles.underlineColor), range);
893 }
894
895 if (decor & TextDecoration::LineThrough) {
896 AXAttributeStringSetNumber(attrString, NSAccessibilityStrikethroughTextAttribute, @YES, range);
897 AXAttributeStringSetColor(attrString, NSAccessibilityStrikethroughColorTextAttribute, nsColor(decorationStyles.linethroughColor), range);
898 }
899 }
900
901 // Indicate background highlighting.
902 for (Node* node = renderer->node(); node; node = node->parentNode()) {
903 if (node->hasTagName(HTMLNames::markTag))
904 AXAttributeStringSetNumber(attrString, @"AXHighlight", @YES, range);
905 }
906}

922static void AXAttributeStringSetSpelling(NSMutableAttributedString* attrString, Node* node, StringView text, NSRange range)
923{
924 ASSERT(node);
925
926 // If this node is not inside editable content, do not run the spell checker on the text.
927 if (!node->document().axObjectCache()->rootAXEditableElement(node))
928 return;
929
930 if (unifiedTextCheckerEnabled(node->document().frame())) {
931 // Check the spelling directly since document->markersForNode() does not store the misspelled marking when the cursor is in a word.
932 TextCheckerClient* checker = node->document().editor().textChecker();
933
934 // checkTextOfParagraph is the only spelling/grammar checker implemented in WK1 and WK2
935 Vector<TextCheckingResult> results;
936 checkTextOfParagraph(*checker, text, TextCheckingType::Spelling, results, node->document().frame()->selection().selection());
937
938 size_t size = results.size();
939 for (unsigned i = 0; i < size; i++) {
940 const TextCheckingResult& result = results[i];
941 AXAttributeStringSetNumber(attrString, NSAccessibilityMisspelledTextAttribute, @YES, NSMakeRange(result.range.location + range.location, result.range.length));
942#if PLATFORM(MAC)
943 AXAttributeStringSetNumber(attrString, NSAccessibilityMarkedMisspelledTextAttribute, @YES, NSMakeRange(result.range.location + range.location, result.range.length));
944#endif
945 }
946 return;
947 }
948
949 for (unsigned currentPosition = 0; currentPosition < text.length(); ) {
950 int misspellingLocation = -1;
951 int misspellingLength = 0;
952 node->document().editor().textChecker()->checkSpellingOfString(text.substring(currentPosition), &misspellingLocation, &misspellingLength);
953 if (misspellingLocation == -1 || !misspellingLength)
954 break;
955
956 NSRange spellRange = NSMakeRange(range.location + currentPosition + misspellingLocation, misspellingLength);
957 AXAttributeStringSetNumber(attrString, NSAccessibilityMisspelledTextAttribute, @YES, spellRange);
958#if PLATFORM(MAC)
959 AXAttributeStringSetNumber(attrString, NSAccessibilityMarkedMisspelledTextAttribute, @YES, spellRange);
960#endif
961
962 currentPosition += misspellingLocation + misspellingLength;
963 }
964}

977static void AXAttributeStringSetHeadingLevel(NSMutableAttributedString* attrString, RenderObject* renderer, NSRange range)
978{
979 if (!renderer)
980 return;
981
982 if (!AXAttributedStringRangeIsValid(attrString, range))
983 return;
984
985 // Sometimes there are objects between the text and the heading.
986 // In those cases the parent hierarchy should be queried to see if there is a heading level.
987 int parentHeadingLevel = 0;
988 AccessibilityObject* parentObject = renderer->document().axObjectCache()->getOrCreate(renderer->parent());
989 for (; parentObject; parentObject = parentObject->parentObject()) {
990 parentHeadingLevel = parentObject->headingLevel();
991 if (parentHeadingLevel)
992 break;
993 }
994
995 if (parentHeadingLevel)
996 [attrString addAttribute:@"AXHeadingLevel" value:@(parentHeadingLevel) range:range];
997 else
998 [attrString removeAttribute:@"AXHeadingLevel" range:range];
999}

1001static void AXAttributeStringSetElement(NSMutableAttributedString* attrString, NSString* attribute, AccessibilityObject* object, NSRange range)
1002{
1003 if (!AXAttributedStringRangeIsValid(attrString, range))
1004 return;
1005
1006 if (is<AccessibilityRenderObject>(object)) {
1007 // make a serializable AX object
1008
1009 RenderObject* renderer = downcast<AccessibilityRenderObject>(*object).renderer();
1010 if (!renderer)
1011 return;
1012
1013 AXObjectCache* cache = renderer->document().axObjectCache();
1014 if (!cache)
1015 return;
1016
1017 id objectWrapper = object->wrapper();
1018 if ([attribute isEqualToString:NSAccessibilityAttachmentTextAttribute] && object->isAttachment() && [objectWrapper attachmentView])
1019 objectWrapper = [objectWrapper attachmentView];
1020
1021 if (auto axElement = adoptCF(NSAccessibilityCreateAXUIElementRef(objectWrapper)))
1022 [attrString addAttribute:attribute value:(__bridge id)axElement.get() range:range];
1023 } else
1024 [attrString removeAttribute:attribute range:range];
1025}
1026
1027static void AXAttributedStringAppendText(NSMutableAttributedString* attrString, Node* node, StringView text, bool spellCheck)
1028{
1029 // skip invisible text
1030 RenderObject* renderer = node->renderer();
1031 if (!renderer || !text.length())
1032 return;
1033
1034 // easier to calculate the range before appending the string
1035 NSRange attrStringRange = NSMakeRange([attrString length], text.length());
1036
1037 // append the string from this node
1038 [[attrString mutableString] appendString:text.createNSStringWithoutCopying().get()];
1039
1040 // add new attributes and remove irrelevant inherited ones
1041 // NOTE: color attributes are handled specially because -[NSMutableAttributedString addAttribute: value: range:] does not merge
1042 // identical colors. Workaround is to not replace an existing color attribute if it matches what we are adding. This also means
1043 // we cannot just pre-remove all inherited attributes on the appended string, so we have to remove the irrelevant ones individually.
1044
1045 // remove inherited attachment from prior AXAttributedStringAppendReplaced
1046 [attrString removeAttribute:NSAccessibilityAttachmentTextAttribute range:attrStringRange];
1047 if (spellCheck) {
1048#if PLATFORM(MAC)
1049 [attrString removeAttribute:NSAccessibilityMarkedMisspelledTextAttribute range:attrStringRange];
1050#endif
1051 [attrString removeAttribute:NSAccessibilityMisspelledTextAttribute range:attrStringRange];
1052 }
1053
1054 // set new attributes
1055 AXAttributeStringSetStyle(attrString, renderer, attrStringRange);
1056 AXAttributeStringSetHeadingLevel(attrString, renderer, attrStringRange);
1057 AXAttributeStringSetBlockquoteLevel(attrString, renderer, attrStringRange);
1058 AXAttributeStringSetExpandedTextValue(attrString, renderer, attrStringRange);
1059 AXAttributeStringSetElement(attrString, NSAccessibilityLinkTextAttribute, AccessibilityObject::anchorElementForNode(node), attrStringRange);
1060
1061 // do spelling last because it tends to break up the range
1062 if (spellCheck)
1063 AXAttributeStringSetSpelling(attrString, node, text, attrStringRange);
1064}
1065
1066static NSString* nsStringForReplacedNode(Node* replacedNode)
1067{
1068 // we should always be given a rendered node and a replaced node, but be safe
1069 // replaced nodes are either attachments (widgets) or images
1070 if (!replacedNode || !isRendererReplacedElement(replacedNode->renderer()) || replacedNode->isTextNode()) {
1071 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1072 return nil;
1073 }
1074
1075 // create an AX object, but skip it if it is not supposed to be seen
1076 RefPtr<AccessibilityObject> obj = replacedNode->renderer()->document().axObjectCache()->getOrCreate(replacedNode->renderer());
1077 if (obj->accessibilityIsIgnored())
1078 return nil;
1079
1080 // use the attachmentCharacter to represent the replaced node
1081 const UniChar attachmentChar = NSAttachmentCharacter;
1082 return [NSString stringWithCharacters:&attachmentChar length:1];
1083}

1085- (NSAttributedString *)doAXAttributedStringForTextMarkerRange:(AXTextMarkerRangeRef)textMarkerRange spellCheck:(BOOL)spellCheck
1086{
1087 return Accessibility::retrieveAutoreleasedValueFromMainThread<NSAttributedString *>([&textMarkerRange, &spellCheck, protectedSelf = retainPtr(self)] () -> RetainPtr<NSAttributedString> {
1088 auto* backingObject = protectedSelf.get().axBackingObject;
1089 if (!backingObject)
1090 return nil;
1091
1092 auto range = rangeForTextMarkerRange(backingObject->axObjectCache(), textMarkerRange);
1093 if (!range)
1094 return nil;
1095 auto attrString = adoptNS([[NSMutableAttributedString alloc] init]);
1096 TextIterator it(*range);
1097 while (!it.atEnd()) {
1098 Node& node = it.range().start.container;
1099
1100 // non-zero length means textual node, zero length means replaced node (AKA "attachments" in AX)
1101 if (it.text().length()) {
1102 // Add the text of the list marker item if necessary.
1103 String listMarkerText = AccessibilityObject::listMarkerTextForNodeAndPosition(&node, makeContainerOffsetPosition(it.range().start));
1104 if (!listMarkerText.isEmpty())
1105 AXAttributedStringAppendText(attrString.get(), &node, listMarkerText, spellCheck);
1106 AXAttributedStringAppendText(attrString.get(), &node, it.text(), spellCheck);
1107 } else {
1108 Node* replacedNode = it.node();
1109 NSString *attachmentString = nsStringForReplacedNode(replacedNode);
1110 if (attachmentString) {
1111 NSRange attrStringRange = NSMakeRange([attrString length], [attachmentString length]);
1112
1113 // append the placeholder string
1114 [[attrString mutableString] appendString:attachmentString];
1115
1116 // remove all inherited attributes
1117 [attrString setAttributes:nil range:attrStringRange];
1118
1119 // add the attachment attribute
1120 AccessibilityObject* obj = replacedNode->renderer()->document().axObjectCache()->getOrCreate(replacedNode->renderer());
1121 AXAttributeStringSetElement(attrString.get(), NSAccessibilityAttachmentTextAttribute, obj, attrStringRange);
1122 }
1123 }
1124 it.advance();
1125 }
1126
1127 return attrString;
1128 });
1129}

1144ALLOW_DEPRECATED_IMPLEMENTATIONS_BEGIN
1145- (NSArray*)accessibilityActionNames
1146ALLOW_DEPRECATED_IMPLEMENTATIONS_END
1147{
1148 auto* backingObject = self.updateObjectBackingStore;
1149 if (!backingObject)
1150 return nil;
1151
1152 // All elements should get ShowMenu and ScrollToVisible.
1153 // But certain earlier VoiceOver versions do not support scroll to visible, and it confuses them to see it in the list.
1154 static NeverDestroyed<RetainPtr<NSArray>> defaultElementActions = @[NSAccessibilityShowMenuAction, NSAccessibilityScrollToVisibleAction];
1155
1156 // Action elements allow Press.
1157 // The order is important to VoiceOver, which expects the 'default' action to be the first action. In this case the default action should be press.
1158 static NeverDestroyed<RetainPtr<NSArray>> actionElementActions = @[NSAccessibilityPressAction, NSAccessibilityShowMenuAction, NSAccessibilityScrollToVisibleAction];
1159
1160 // Menu elements allow Press and Cancel.
1161 static NeverDestroyed<RetainPtr<NSArray>> menuElementActions = [actionElementActions.get() arrayByAddingObject:NSAccessibilityCancelAction];
1162
1163 // Slider elements allow Increment/Decrement.
1164 static NeverDestroyed<RetainPtr<NSArray>> sliderActions = [defaultElementActions.get() arrayByAddingObjectsFromArray:@[NSAccessibilityIncrementAction, NSAccessibilityDecrementAction]];
1165
1166 NSArray *actions;
1167 if (backingObject->supportsPressAction())
1168 actions = actionElementActions.get().get();
1169 else if (backingObject->isMenuRelated())
1170 actions = menuElementActions.get().get();
1171 else if (backingObject->isSlider())
1172 actions = sliderActions.get().get();
1173 else if (backingObject->isAttachment())
1174 actions = [[self attachmentView] accessibilityActionNames];
1175 else
1176 actions = defaultElementActions.get().get();
1177
1178 return actions;
1179}

1575 NSArray *objectAttributes = attributes.get().get();
1576
1577 if (backingObject->isPasswordField())
1578 objectAttributes = passwordFieldAttrs.get().get();
1579 else if (backingObject->isWebArea())
1580 objectAttributes = webAreaAttrs.get().get();
1581 else if (backingObject->isTextControl())
1582 objectAttributes = textAttrs.get().get();
1583 else if (backingObject->isLink())
1584 objectAttributes = anchorAttrs.get().get();
1585 else if (backingObject->isImage())
1586 objectAttributes = imageAttrs.get().get();
1587 else if (backingObject->isTable() && backingObject->isExposable())
1588 objectAttributes = tableAttrs.get().get();
1589 else if (backingObject->isTableColumn())
1590 objectAttributes = tableColAttrs.get().get();
1591 else if (backingObject->isTableCell())
1592 objectAttributes = tableCellAttrs.get().get();
1593 else if (backingObject->isTableRow()) {
1594 // An ARIA table row can be collapsed and expanded, so it needs the extra attributes.
1595 if (backingObject->isARIATreeGridRow())
1596 objectAttributes = outlineRowAttrs.get().get();
1597 else
1598 objectAttributes = tableRowAttrs.get().get();
1599 } else if (backingObject->isTree())
1600 objectAttributes = outlineAttrs.get().get();
1601 else if (backingObject->isTreeItem()) {
1602 if (backingObject->supportsCheckedState())
1603 objectAttributes = [outlineRowAttrs.get() arrayByAddingObject:NSAccessibilityValueAttribute];
1604 else
1605 objectAttributes = outlineRowAttrs.get().get();
1606 }
1607 else if (backingObject->isListBox())
1608 objectAttributes = listBoxAttrs.get().get();
1609 else if (backingObject->isList())
1610 objectAttributes = listAttrs.get().get();
1611 else if (backingObject->isComboBox())
1612 objectAttributes = comboBoxAttrs.get().get();
1613 else if (backingObject->isProgressIndicator() || backingObject->isSlider())
1614 objectAttributes = rangeAttrs.get().get();
1615 // These are processed in order because an input image is a button, and a button is a control.
1616 else if (backingObject->isInputImage())
1617 objectAttributes = inputImageAttrs.get().get();
1618 else if (backingObject->isButton())
1619 objectAttributes = buttonAttrs.get().get();
1620 else if (backingObject->isControl())
1621 objectAttributes = controlAttrs.get().get();
1622
1623 else if (backingObject->isGroup() || backingObject->isListItem())
1624 objectAttributes = groupAttrs.get().get();
1625 else if (backingObject->isTabList())
1626 objectAttributes = tabListAttrs.get().get();
1627 else if (backingObject->isScrollView())
1628 objectAttributes = scrollViewAttrs.get().get();
1629 else if (backingObject->isSpinButton())
1630 objectAttributes = incrementorAttrs.get().get();
1631 else if (backingObject->isMenu())
1632 objectAttributes = menuAttrs.get().get();
1633 else if (backingObject->isMenuBar())
1634 objectAttributes = menuBarAttrs.get().get();
1635 else if (backingObject->isMenuButton())
1636 objectAttributes = menuButtonAttrs.get().get();
1637 else if (backingObject->isMenuItem())
1638 objectAttributes = menuItemAttrs.get().get();
1639
1640 NSArray *additionalAttributes = [self additionalAccessibilityAttributeNames];
1641 if ([additionalAttributes count])
1642 objectAttributes = [objectAttributes arrayByAddingObjectsFromArray:additionalAttributes];
1643
1644 // Only expose AXARIACurrent attribute when the element is set to be current item.
1645 if (backingObject->currentState() != AccessibilityCurrentState::False)
1646 objectAttributes = [objectAttributes arrayByAddingObjectsFromArray:@[ NSAccessibilityARIACurrentAttribute ]];
1647
1648 // AppKit needs to know the screen height in order to do the coordinate conversion.
1649 objectAttributes = [objectAttributes arrayByAddingObjectsFromArray:@[ NSAccessibilityPrimaryScreenHeightAttribute ]];
1650
1651 return objectAttributes;
1652}

1671static void convertToVector(NSArray* array, AccessibilityObject::AccessibilityChildrenVector& vector)
1672{
1673 unsigned length = [array count];
1674 vector.reserveInitialCapacity(length);
1675 for (unsigned i = 0; i < length; ++i) {
1676 AXCoreObject* obj = [[array objectAtIndex:i] axBackingObject];
1677 if (obj)
1678 vector.append(obj);
1679 }
1680}

1697- (id)associatedPluginParent
1698{
1699 return Accessibility::retrieveAutoreleasedValueFromMainThread<id>([protectedSelf = retainPtr(self)] () -> RetainPtr<id> {
1700 auto* backingObject = protectedSelf.get().axBackingObject;
1701 if (!backingObject || !backingObject->hasApplePDFAnnotationAttribute())
1702 return nil;
1703
1704 if (!backingObject->document()->isPluginDocument())
1705 return nil;
1706
1707 Widget* pluginWidget = static_cast<PluginDocument*>(backingObject->document())->pluginWidget();
1708 if (!pluginWidget || !pluginWidget->isPluginViewBase())
1709 return nil;
1710
1711 return static_cast<PluginViewBase*>(pluginWidget)->accessibilityAssociatedPluginParentForElement(backingObject->element());
1712 });
1713}

1715static void WebTransformCGPathToNSBezierPath(void* info, const CGPathElement *element)
1716{
1717 NSBezierPath *bezierPath = (__bridge NSBezierPath *)info;
1718 switch (element->type) {
1719 case kCGPathElementMoveToPoint:
1720 [bezierPath moveToPoint:NSPointFromCGPoint(element->points[0])];
1721 break;
1722 case kCGPathElementAddLineToPoint:
1723 [bezierPath lineToPoint:NSPointFromCGPoint(element->points[0])];
1724 break;
1725 case kCGPathElementAddCurveToPoint:
1726 [bezierPath curveToPoint:NSPointFromCGPoint(element->points[0]) controlPoint1:NSPointFromCGPoint(element->points[1]) controlPoint2:NSPointFromCGPoint(element->points[2])];
1727 break;
1728 case kCGPathElementCloseSubpath:
1729 [bezierPath closePath];
1730 break;
1731 default:
1732 break;
1733 }
1734}
1735
1736- (NSBezierPath *)bezierPathFromPath:(CGPathRef)path
1737{
1738 NSBezierPath *bezierPath = [NSBezierPath bezierPath];
1739 CGPathApply(path, (__bridge void*)bezierPath, WebTransformCGPathToNSBezierPath);
1740 return bezierPath;
1741}
1742
1743- (NSBezierPath *)path
1744{
1745 Path path = self.axBackingObject->elementPath();
1746 if (path.isEmpty())
1747 return NULL;
1748
1749 CGPathRef transformedPath = [self convertPathToScreenSpace:path];
1750 return [self bezierPathFromPath:transformedPath];
1751}

1773- (NSValue *)position
1774{
1775 auto* backingObject = self.axBackingObject;
1776 if (!backingObject)
1777 return nil;
1778
1779 auto rect = snappedIntRect(backingObject->elementRect());
1780
1781 // The Cocoa accessibility API wants the lower-left corner.
1782 FloatPoint floatPoint(rect.x(), rect.maxY());
1783
1784 // FIXME: add a function to convert a point, no need to convert a rect when you only need a point.
1785 FloatRect floatRect(floatPoint, FloatSize());
1786 CGRect cgRect(backingObject->convertRectToPlatformSpace(floatRect, AccessibilityConversionSpace::Screen));
1787 return @(cgRect.origin);
1788}

1804- (NSString*)subrole
1805{
1806 auto* backingObject = self.axBackingObject;
1807 if (!backingObject)
1808 return nil;
1809
1810 // FIXME: create AXCoreObject::subrolePlatformString to replace the following linear search and heuristics, similar to rolePlatformString.
1811 if (backingObject->isPasswordField())
1812 return NSAccessibilitySecureTextFieldSubrole;
1813 if (backingObject->isSearchField())
1814 return NSAccessibilitySearchFieldSubrole;
1815
1816 if (backingObject->isAttachment()) {
1817 NSView* attachView = [self attachmentView];
1818 if ([[attachView accessibilityAttributeNames] containsObject:NSAccessibilitySubroleAttribute])
1819 return [attachView accessibilityAttributeValue:NSAccessibilitySubroleAttribute];
1820 }
1821
1822 if (backingObject->isMeter())
1823 return @"AXMeter";
1824
1825 AccessibilityRole role = backingObject->roleValue();
1826 if (role == AccessibilityRole::HorizontalRule)
1827 return NSAccessibilityContentSeparatorSubrole;
1828 if (role == AccessibilityRole::ToggleButton)
1829 return NSAccessibilityToggleSubrole;
1830 if (role == AccessibilityRole::Footer)
1831 return @"AXFooter";
1832 if (role == AccessibilityRole::SpinButtonPart) {
1833 if (backingObject->isIncrementor())
1834 return NSAccessibilityIncrementArrowSubrole;
1835 return NSAccessibilityDecrementArrowSubrole;
1836 }
1837
1838 if (backingObject->isFileUploadButton())
1839 return @"AXFileUploadButton";
1840
1841 if (backingObject->isTreeItem())
1842 return NSAccessibilityOutlineRowSubrole;
1843
1844 if (backingObject->isFieldset())
1845 return @"AXFieldset";
1846
1847 if (backingObject->isList()) {
1848 if (backingObject->isUnorderedList() || backingObject->isOrderedList())
1849 return NSAccessibilityContentListSubrole;
1850 if (backingObject->isDescriptionList()) {
1851 return NSAccessibilityDescriptionListSubrole;
1852 }
1853 }
1854
1855 // ARIA content subroles.
1856 switch (role) {
1857 case AccessibilityRole::LandmarkBanner:
1858 return @"AXLandmarkBanner";
1859 case AccessibilityRole::LandmarkComplementary:
1860 return @"AXLandmarkComplementary";
1861 case AccessibilityRole::LandmarkContentInfo:
1862 return @"AXLandmarkContentInfo";
1863 case AccessibilityRole::LandmarkMain:
1864 return @"AXLandmarkMain";
1865 case AccessibilityRole::LandmarkNavigation:
1866 return @"AXLandmarkNavigation";
1867 case AccessibilityRole::LandmarkDocRegion:
1868 case AccessibilityRole::LandmarkRegion:
1869 return @"AXLandmarkRegion";
1870 case AccessibilityRole::LandmarkSearch:
1871 return @"AXLandmarkSearch";
1872 case AccessibilityRole::ApplicationAlert:
1873 return @"AXApplicationAlert";
1874 case AccessibilityRole::ApplicationAlertDialog:
1875 return @"AXApplicationAlertDialog";
1876 case AccessibilityRole::ApplicationDialog:
1877 return @"AXApplicationDialog";
1878 case AccessibilityRole::ApplicationGroup:
1879 case AccessibilityRole::ApplicationTextGroup:
1880 case AccessibilityRole::Feed:

2019- (NSString*)roleDescription
2020{
2021 auto* backingObject = self.axBackingObject;
2022 if (!backingObject)
2023 return nil;
2024
2025 ALLOW_DEPRECATED_DECLARATIONS_BEGIN
2026 // attachments have the AXImage role, but a different subrole
2027 if (backingObject->isAttachment())
2028 return [[self attachmentView] accessibilityAttributeValue:NSAccessibilityRoleDescriptionAttribute];
2029 ALLOW_DEPRECATED_DECLARATIONS_END
2030
2031 String roleDescription = backingObject->roleDescription();
2032 if (!roleDescription.isEmpty())
2033 return roleDescription;
2034
2035 NSString *axRole = backingObject->rolePlatformString();
2036 NSString *subrole = self.subrole;
2037 // Fallback to the system default role description.
2038 // If we get the same string back, then as a last resort, return unknown.
2039 NSString *defaultRoleDescription = NSAccessibilityRoleDescription(axRole, subrole);
2040
2041 // On earlier Mac versions (Lion), using a non-standard subrole would result in a role description
2042 // being returned that looked like AXRole:AXSubrole. To make all platforms have the same role descriptions
2043 // we should fallback on a role description ignoring the subrole in these cases.
2044 if ([defaultRoleDescription isEqualToString:[NSString stringWithFormat:@"%@:%@", axRole, subrole]])
2045 defaultRoleDescription = NSAccessibilityRoleDescription(axRole, nil);
2046
2047 if (![defaultRoleDescription isEqualToString:axRole])
2048 return defaultRoleDescription;
2049
2050 return NSAccessibilityRoleDescription(NSAccessibilityUnknownRole, nil);
2051}

2053- (NSString *)computedRoleString
2054{
2055 if (!self.axBackingObject)
2056 return nil;
2057 return self.axBackingObject->computedRoleString();
2058}

2060- (id)scrollViewParent
2061{
2062 auto* backingObject = self.axBackingObject;
2063 if (!backingObject || !backingObject->isScrollView())
2064 return nil;
2065
2066 // If this scroll view provides it's parent object (because it's a sub-frame), then
2067 // we should not find the remoteAccessibilityParent.
2068 if (backingObject->parentObject())
2069 return nil;
2070
2071 if (auto platformWidget = backingObject->platformWidget())
2072 return NSAccessibilityUnignoredAncestor(platformWidget);
2073
2074 return backingObject->remoteParentObject();
2075}

3198- (void)_accessibilityShowContextMenu
3199{
3200 ASSERT(isMainThread());
3201
3202 if (!self.axBackingObject)
3203 return;
3204
3205 Page* page = self.axBackingObject->page();
3206 if (!page)
3207 return;
3208
3209 IntRect rect = snappedIntRect(self.axBackingObject->elementRect());
3210 FrameView* frameView = self.axBackingObject->documentFrameView();
3211
3212 // On WK2, we need to account for the scroll position with regards to root view.
3213 // On WK1, we need to convert rect to window space to match mouse clicking.
3214 if (frameView) {
3215 // Find the appropriate scroll view to use to convert the contents to the window.
3216 for (auto* parent = self.axBackingObject->parentObject(); parent; parent = parent->parentObject()) {
3217 if (parent->isScrollView()) {
3218 if (auto* scrollView = parent->scrollView()) {
3219 if (!frameView->platformWidget())
3220 rect = scrollView->contentsToRootView(rect);
3221 else
3222 rect = scrollView->contentsToWindow(rect);
3223 }
3224 break;
3225 }
3226 }
3227 }
3228
3229 page->contextMenuController().showContextMenuAt(page->mainFrame(), rect.center());
3230}

3311- (void)_accessibilitySetValue:(id)value forAttribute:(NSString *)attributeName
3312{
3313 AXTRACE(makeString("WebAccessibilityObjectWrapper _accessibilitySetValue: forAttribute:", String(attributeName)));
3314
3315 auto* backingObject = self.updateObjectBackingStore;
3316 if (!backingObject) {
3317 AXLOG("No backingObject!!!");
3318 return;
3319 }
3320
3321 AXTextMarkerRangeRef textMarkerRange = nil;
3322 NSNumber* number = nil;
3323 NSString* string = nil;
3324 NSRange range = {0, 0};
3325 NSArray* array = nil;
3326
3327 // decode the parameter
3328 if (AXObjectIsTextMarkerRange(value))
3329 textMarkerRange = (AXTextMarkerRangeRef)value;
3330 else if ([value isKindOfClass:[NSNumber class]])
3331 number = value;
3332 else if ([value isKindOfClass:[NSString class]])
3333 string = value;
3334 else if ([value isKindOfClass:[NSValue class]])
3335 range = [value rangeValue];
3336 else if ([value isKindOfClass:[NSArray class]])
3337 array = value;
3338
3339 // handle the command
3340 if ([attributeName isEqualToString: @"AXSelectedTextMarkerRange"]) {
3341 ASSERT(textMarkerRange);
3342 Accessibility::performFunctionOnMainThread([&textMarkerRange, protectedSelf = retainPtr(self)] {
3343 if (auto* backingObject = protectedSelf.get().axBackingObject)
3344 backingObject->setSelectedVisiblePositionRange(visiblePositionRangeForTextMarkerRange(backingObject->axObjectCache(), textMarkerRange));
3345 });
3346 } else if ([attributeName isEqualToString: NSAccessibilityFocusedAttribute]) {
3347 backingObject->setFocused([number boolValue]);
3348 } else if ([attributeName isEqualToString: NSAccessibilityValueAttribute]) {
3349 if (number && backingObject->canSetNumericValue())
3350 backingObject->setValue([number floatValue]);
3351 else if (string)
3352 backingObject->setValue(string);
3353 } else if ([attributeName isEqualToString: NSAccessibilitySelectedAttribute]) {
3354 if (!number)
3355 return;
3356 backingObject->setSelected([number boolValue]);
3357 } else if ([attributeName isEqualToString:NSAccessibilitySelectedChildrenAttribute]) {
3358 if (!array || !backingObject->canSetSelectedChildren())
3359 return;
3360
3361 AXCoreObject::AccessibilityChildrenVector selectedChildren;
3362 convertToVector(array, selectedChildren);
3363 backingObject->setSelectedChildren(selectedChildren);
3364 } else if (backingObject->isTextControl()) {
3365 if ([attributeName isEqualToString: NSAccessibilitySelectedTextAttribute]) {
3366 backingObject->setSelectedText(string);
3367 } else if ([attributeName isEqualToString: NSAccessibilitySelectedTextRangeAttribute]) {
3368 backingObject->setSelectedTextRange(PlainTextRange(range.location, range.length));
3369 } else if ([attributeName isEqualToString: NSAccessibilityVisibleCharacterRangeAttribute]) {
3370 backingObject->makeRangeVisible(PlainTextRange(range.location, range.length));
3371 }
3372 } else if ([attributeName isEqualToString:NSAccessibilityDisclosingAttribute] || [attributeName isEqualToString:NSAccessibilityExpandedAttribute])
3373 backingObject->setIsExpanded([number boolValue]);
3374 else if ([attributeName isEqualToString:NSAccessibilitySelectedRowsAttribute]) {
3375 AccessibilityObject::AccessibilityChildrenVector selectedRows;
3376 convertToVector(array, selectedRows);
3377 if (backingObject->isTree() || (backingObject->isTable() && backingObject->isExposable()))
3378 backingObject->setSelectedRows(selectedRows);
3379 } else if ([attributeName isEqualToString:NSAccessibilityGrabbedAttribute])
3380 backingObject->setARIAGrabbed([number boolValue]);
3381 else if (backingObject->isWebArea() && [attributeName isEqualToString:NSAccessibilityPreventKeyboardDOMEventDispatchAttribute])
3382 backingObject->setPreventKeyboardDOMEventDispatch([number boolValue]);
3383 else if (backingObject->isWebArea() && [attributeName isEqualToString:NSAccessibilityCaretBrowsingEnabledAttribute])

3692ALLOW_DEPRECATED_IMPLEMENTATIONS_BEGIN
3693- (id)accessibilityAttributeValue:(NSString*)attribute forParameter:(id)parameter
3694ALLOW_DEPRECATED_IMPLEMENTATIONS_END
3695{
3696 AXTRACE(makeString("WebAccessibilityObjectWrapper accessibilityAttributeValue:", String(attribute)));
3697 auto* backingObject = self.updateObjectBackingStore;
3698 if (!backingObject)
3699 return nil;
3700
3701 // Basic parameter validation.
3702 if (!attribute || !parameter)
3703 return nil;
3704
3705 AXTextMarkerRef textMarker = nil;
3706 AXTextMarkerRangeRef textMarkerRange = nil;
3707 NSNumber* number = nil;
3708 NSArray* array = nil;
3709 NSDictionary* dictionary = nil;
3710 RefPtr<AXCoreObject> uiElement;
3711 NSPoint point = NSZeroPoint;
3712 bool pointSet = false;
3713 NSRange range = {0, 0};
3714 bool rangeSet = false;
3715 NSRect rect = NSZeroRect;
3716
3717 // common parameter type check/casting. Nil checks in handlers catch wrong type case.
3718 // NOTE: This assumes nil is not a valid parameter, because it is indistinguishable from
3719 // a parameter of the wrong type.
3720 if (AXObjectIsTextMarker(parameter))
3721 textMarker = (AXTextMarkerRef)parameter;
3722 else if (AXObjectIsTextMarkerRange(parameter))
3723 textMarkerRange = (AXTextMarkerRangeRef)parameter;
3724 else if ([parameter isKindOfClass:[WebAccessibilityObjectWrapper class]])
3725 uiElement = [(WebAccessibilityObjectWrapper*)parameter axBackingObject];
3726 else if ([parameter isKindOfClass:[NSNumber class]])
3727 number = parameter;
3728 else if ([parameter isKindOfClass:[NSArray class]])
3729 array = parameter;
3730 else if ([parameter isKindOfClass:[NSDictionary class]])
3731 dictionary = parameter;
3732 else if ([parameter isKindOfClass:[NSValue class]] && !strcmp([(NSValue*)parameter objCType], @encode(NSPoint))) {
3733 pointSet = true;
3734 point = [(NSValue*)parameter pointValue];
3735 } else if ([parameter isKindOfClass:[NSValue class]] && !strcmp([(NSValue*)parameter objCType], @encode(NSRange))) {
3736 rangeSet = true;
3737 range = [(NSValue*)parameter rangeValue];
3738 } else if ([parameter isKindOfClass:[NSValue class]] && !strcmp([(NSValue*)parameter objCType], @encode(NSRect)))
3739 rect = [(NSValue*)parameter rectValue];
3740 else {
3741 // Attribute type is not supported. Allow super to handle.
3742 return [super accessibilityAttributeValue:attribute forParameter:parameter];
3743 }
3744
3745 // dispatch
3746 if ([attribute isEqualToString:NSAccessibilitySelectTextWithCriteriaParameterizedAttribute]) {
3747 // To be deprecated.
3748 auto result = Accessibility::retrieveValueFromMainThread<Vector<String>>([dictionary, protectedSelf = retainPtr(self)] () -> Vector<String> {
3749 auto* backingObject = protectedSelf.get().axBackingObject;
3750 if (!backingObject)
3751 return Vector<String>();
3752
3753 auto criteria = accessibilityTextCriteriaForParameterizedAttribute(dictionary);
3754 criteria.second.textRanges = backingObject->findTextRanges(criteria.first);
3755 ASSERT(criteria.second.textRanges.size() <= 1);
3756 return backingObject->performTextOperation(criteria.second);
3757 });
3758 ASSERT(result.size() <= 1);
3759 if (result.size() > 0)
3760 return result[0];
3761 return String();
3762 }
3763
3764 if ([attribute isEqualToString:NSAccessibilitySearchTextWithCriteriaParameterizedAttribute]) {
3765 auto criteria = accessibilitySearchTextCriteriaForParameterizedAttribute(dictionary);
3766 return Accessibility::retrieveAutoreleasedValueFromMainThread<NSArray *>([&criteria, protectedSelf = retainPtr(self)] () -> RetainPtr<NSArray> {
3767 auto* backingObject = protectedSelf.get().axBackingObject;
3768 if (!backingObject)
3769 return nil;
3770 auto ranges = backingObject->findTextRanges(criteria);
3771 if (ranges.isEmpty())
3772 return nil;
3773 return createNSArray(ranges, [&] (auto& range) {
3774 return (id)textMarkerRangeFromRange(backingObject->axObjectCache(), range);
3775 }).autorelease();
3776 });
3777 }
3778
3779 if ([attribute isEqualToString:NSAccessibilityTextOperationParameterizedAttribute]) {
3780 auto operationResult = Accessibility::retrieveValueFromMainThread<Vector<String>>([dictionary, protectedSelf = retainPtr(self)] () -> Vector<String> {
3781 auto* backingObject = protectedSelf.get().axBackingObject;
3782 if (!backingObject)
3783 return Vector<String>();
3784
3785 auto textOperation = accessibilityTextOperationForParameterizedAttribute(backingObject->axObjectCache(), dictionary);
3786 return backingObject->performTextOperation(textOperation);
3787 });
3788 if (operationResult.isEmpty())
3789 return nil;
3790 return createNSArray(operationResult).autorelease();
3791 }
3792
3793 if ([attribute isEqualToString:NSAccessibilityUIElementCountForSearchPredicateParameterizedAttribute]) {
3794 AccessibilitySearchCriteria criteria = accessibilitySearchCriteriaForSearchPredicateParameterizedAttribute(dictionary);
3795 AccessibilityObject::AccessibilityChildrenVector results;
3796 backingObject->findMatchingObjects(&criteria, results);
3797 return @(results.size());
3798 }
3799
3800 if ([attribute isEqualToString:NSAccessibilityUIElementsForSearchPredicateParameterizedAttribute]) {
3801 AccessibilitySearchCriteria criteria = accessibilitySearchCriteriaForSearchPredicateParameterizedAttribute(dictionary);
3802 AccessibilityObject::AccessibilityChildrenVector results;
3803 backingObject->findMatchingObjects(&criteria, results);
3804 return convertToNSArray(results);
3805 }
3806
3807 // TextMarker attributes.

4291// API that AppKit uses for faster access
4292- (NSUInteger)accessibilityIndexOfChild:(id)child
4293{
4294 auto* backingObject = self.updateObjectBackingStore;
4295 if (!backingObject)
4296 return NSNotFound;
4297
4298 // Tree objects return their rows as their children. We can use the original method
4299 // here, because we won't gain any speed up.
4300 if (backingObject->isTree())
4301 return [super accessibilityIndexOfChild:child];
4302
4303 NSArray *children = self.childrenVectorArray;
4304 if (!children.count)
4305 return [[self renderWidgetChildren] indexOfObject:child];
4306
4307 NSUInteger count = [children count];
4308 for (NSUInteger i = 0; i < count; ++i) {
4309 WebAccessibilityObjectWrapper *wrapper = children[i];
4310 auto* object = wrapper.axBackingObject;
4311 if (!object)
4312 continue;
4313
4314 if (wrapper == child || (object->isAttachment() && [wrapper attachmentView] == child))
4315 return i;
4316 }
4317
4318 return NSNotFound;
4319}

4322- (NSUInteger)accessibilityArrayAttributeCount:(NSString *)attribute
4323{
4324 auto* backingObject = self.updateObjectBackingStore;
4325 if (!backingObject)
4326 return 0;
4327
4328 if ([attribute isEqualToString:NSAccessibilityChildrenAttribute]) {
4329 // Tree items object returns a different set of children than those that are in children()
4330 // because an AXOutline (the mac role is becomes) has some odd stipulations.
4331 if (backingObject->isTree() || backingObject->isTreeItem())
4332 return [[self accessibilityAttributeValue:NSAccessibilityChildrenAttribute] count];
4333
4334 auto childrenSize = self.childrenVectorSize;
4335 if (!childrenSize)
4336 return [[self renderWidgetChildren] count];
4337
4338 return childrenSize;
4339 }
4340
4341 return [super accessibilityArrayAttributeCount:attribute];
4342}

4345- (NSArray *)accessibilityArrayAttributeValues:(NSString *)attribute index:(NSUInteger)index maxCount:(NSUInteger)maxCount
4346{
4347 AXTRACE(makeString("WebAccessibilityObjectWrapper accessibilityArrayAttributeValue:", String(attribute)));
4348 auto* backingObject = self.updateObjectBackingStore;
4349 if (!backingObject)
4350 return nil;
4351
4352 if ([attribute isEqualToString:NSAccessibilityChildrenAttribute]) {
4353 if (!self.childrenVectorSize) {
4354 NSArray *children = [self renderWidgetChildren];
4355 if (!children)
4356 return nil;
4357
4358 NSUInteger childCount = [children count];
4359 if (index >= childCount)
4360 return nil;
4361
4362 NSUInteger arrayLength = std::min(childCount - index, maxCount);
4363 return [children subarrayWithRange:NSMakeRange(index, arrayLength)];
4364 }
4365
4366 if (backingObject->isTree() || backingObject->isTreeItem()) {
4367 // Tree objects return their rows as their children & tree items return their contents sans rows.
4368 // We can use the original method in this case.
4369 return [super accessibilityArrayAttributeValues:attribute index:index maxCount:maxCount];
4370 }
4371
4372 auto children = self.childrenVectorArray;
4373 unsigned childCount = [children count];
4374 if (index >= childCount)
4375 return nil;
4376
4377 unsigned available = std::min(childCount - index, maxCount);
4378
4379 NSMutableArray *subarray = [NSMutableArray arrayWithCapacity:available];
4380 for (unsigned added = 0; added < available; ++index, ++added) {
4381 WebAccessibilityObjectWrapper* wrapper = children[index];
4382 // The attachment view should be returned, otherwise AX palindrome errors occur.
4383 BOOL isAttachment = [wrapper isKindOfClass:[WebAccessibilityObjectWrapper class]] && wrapper.axBackingObject && wrapper.axBackingObject->isAttachment() && [wrapper attachmentView];
4384 [subarray addObject:isAttachment ? [wrapper attachmentView] : wrapper];
4385 }
4386
4387 return subarray;
4388 }
4389
4390 return [super accessibilityArrayAttributeValues:attribute index:index maxCount:maxCount];
4391}
